        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:35PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 335 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Ringgold, or 17 miles southeast of Bossier City,
moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mc Dade, Ninock, Elm Grove, Caspiana, Lake Bistineau South, Koran
and Curtis.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
